      "span_text": "A common and fundamental goal is understanding the relative importance of X 1 and X 2 in terms of their association with Y. A typical mistake in neuroscience is to perform two separate tests of associations, one between X 1 and Y, another between X 2 and Y, without explicitly comparing the association strengths between the independent variables  ."
